text: Matúš Sukeľ (born 23 January 1996) is a Slovak professional ice hockey forward who is currently playing under contract with HC Sparta Prague in Czech Extraliga. He was selected and competed in the 2018 Winter Olympics for Slovakia. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Ice hockey players at the 2018 Winter Olympics Category:Slovak ice hockey centres Category:Olympic ice hockey players of Slovakia Category:HC Slovan Bratislava players Category:Sportspeople from Liptovský Mikuláš
